OL,3,CAndy Burnham backs plans for tourist
OL,4,Ctax
OL,6,F"We're giving our mayors powers to
OL,7,Fharness this and put more money into
OL,8,Flocal priorities, so they can keep
OL,9,Fdriving growth and investing in these
OL,10,Fcommunities for years to come."
OL,12,FOfficials said the measure would bring
OL,13,FEnglish cities into line with other
OL,14,Ftourist destinations around the world
OL,15,Fincluding New York, Paris and Milan,
OL,16,Fwhich already charge a tourist tax.
OL,18,FThe Ministry of Housing, Communities
OL,19,Fand Local Government said research
OL,20,Fshowed that "reasonable" fees had a
OL,21,F"minimal" impact on visitor numbers.
